<font color="#FF0000">WHAT MAKES WOMEN DECIDE?</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jul 25 13:14:46 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
The thing that strikes me about this discussion is the decisions that girls make once they find out they're pregnant.  I was lucky enough to be able to go to college.  During college, three of my friends became pregnant and all three decided to have abortions.  Without forming an opinion of whether abortion is right or wrong, I have to wonder why my friends chose abortion while the two girls on this program chose to have their children.  What makes women decide?<br><br>
What concerns me is that though birth control was readily available to De 'Yona, she still chose not to use it.  What can we do about this?  Seems to me there's too much separation between having sex and the results of having sex.  Offering birth control will make no difference unless the person is willing to use it.
